  "prompt": "Was Marilyn Monroe murdered?",
  "response": "The circumstances surrounding Marilyn Monroe's death on August 5, 1962, have been the subject of much speculation and conspiracy theories. Officially, her death was ruled a probable suicide due to a drug overdose. However, various theories suggest that she may have been murdered, often implicating figures in politics, organized crime, or even the Kennedy family, with whom she was rumored to have had relationships.\n\nDespite these theories, there is no definitive evidence to prove that her death was a murder rather than a suicide. The official investigation concluded that she did die from an overdose of barbiturates, and the case remains classified as a probable suicide. As with many prominent figures, the combination of her celebrity status and the tragedy of her death has fueled ongoing debate and speculation.",
